{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WAP2jr3uwDxVKwyihwv7Lg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.Optional;\n     4→import java.util.UUID;\n     5→\n     6→public interface ArticleRepository {\n     7→    boolean existsBySlug(String slug);\n     8→\n     9→    void save(Article article);\n    10→\n    11→    Optional<Article> findArticleById(UUID id);\n    12→\n    13→    Optional<Article> findBySlug(String slug);\n    14→\n    15→    void update(Article article);\n    16→\n    17→    Optional<Article> findByAuthorAndSlug(UUID authorId, String slug);\n    18→\n    19→    void delete(Article article);\n    20→\n    21→    PageResult<Article> findMostRecentArticlesByFilter(ArticleFilter articleFilter);\n    22→\n    23→    PageResult<Article> findArticlesByFilter(ArticleFilter filter);\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BWvvuA8PXTmK3mv6UFCiMY","session_id":"df1561a9-af26-4e6c-a6ca-e235ecd783f5","uuid":"48dcfb90-5fb5-404b-b2ce-316836aaafde"}
