{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01M1qCDmpUrrGF7aJC7ELcM2","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.validator;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import jakarta.validation.ConstraintViolation;\n     6→import jakarta.validation.Validator;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.ModelValidationException;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.Set;\n    10→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n    11→\n    12→@Singleton\n    13→public class ModelValidator {\n    14→\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private Validator validator;\n    17→\n    18→    public <T> T validate(T model) {\n    19→        Set<ConstraintViolation<T>> constraintViolations = validator.validate(model);\n    20→\n    21→        if (!constraintViolations.isEmpty()) {\n    22→            final var messages =\n    23→                    constraintViolations.stream()\n    24→                            .map(ConstraintViolation::getMessage)\n    25→                            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    26→            throw new ModelValidationException(messages);\n    27→        }\n    28→\n    29→        return model;\n    30→    }\n    31→}\n    32→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BWvvuA8PXTmK3mv6UFCiMY","session_id":"df1561a9-af26-4e6c-a6ca-e235ecd783f5","uuid":"1b0ae95e-45e2-43c7-9abd-07a6ef208395"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Eto9iwyDHd8EUB3TVuE7rY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception;\n     2→\n     3→import lombok.Data;\n     4→\n     5→import java.util.LinkedList;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→\n     8→import static java.util.Collections.singletonList;\n     9→\n    10→@Data\n    11→public class BusinessException extends RuntimeException {\n    12→\n    13→  private final int code;\n    14→  private final List<String> messages;\n    15→\n    16→  public BusinessException(int code, String message) {\n    17→    super(message);\n    18→    this.code = code;\n    19→    this.messages = new LinkedList<>(singletonList(message));\n    20→  }\n    21→\n    22→  public BusinessException(int code, List<String> messages) {\n    23→    super(String.join(\", \", messages));\n    24→    this.code = code;\n    25→    this.messages = messages;\n    26→  }\n    27→}\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BWvvuA8PXTmK3mv6UFCiMY","session_id":"df1561a9-af26-4e6c-a6ca-e235ecd783f5","uuid":"ee26abd3-f0ce-480e-a0cf-adfdadd1aaf1"}
