{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MzCcEbyuZRsBmLzZtfgEWG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserByUsername;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.UnfollowUserByUsername;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.FollowRelationshipRepository;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.UUID;\n    11→\n    12→@Singleton\n    13→public class UnfollowUserByUsernameImpl implements UnfollowUserByUsername {\n    14→\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private FindUserById findUserById;\n    17→    @Inject\n    18→    private FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername;\n    19→    @Inject\n    20→    private FollowRelationshipRepository followRelationshipRepository;\n    21→\n    22→    @Override\n    23→    public void handle(UUID loggedUserId, String username) {\n    24→        final var loggedUser = findUserById.handle(loggedUserId);\n    25→        final var userToUnfollow = findUserByUsername.handle(username);\n    26→        final var followingRelationship =\n    27→                followRelationshipRepository.findByUsers(loggedUser, userToUnfollow).orElseThrow();\n    28→        followRelationshipRepository.remove(followingRelationship);\n    29→    }\n    30→}\n    31→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BWvvuA8PXTmK3mv6UFCiMY","session_id":"df1561a9-af26-4e6c-a6ca-e235ecd783f5","uuid":"2e5151e1-