{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011NvHRoFC3dYHwQiJ6XyNDJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.UserNotFoundException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserRepository;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.UUID;\n    11→\n    12→@Singleton\n    13→public class FindUserByIdImpl implements FindUserById {\n    14→\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private UserRepository userRepository;\n    17→\n    18→    @Override\n    19→    public User handle(UUID id) {\n    20→        return userRepository.findUserById(id).orElseThrow(UserNotFoundException::new);\n    21→    }\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BWvvuA8PXTmK3mv6UFCiMY","session_id":"df1561a9-af26-4e6c-a6ca-e235ecd783f5","uuid":"52a9e6cc-4920-4f90-a383-bc977a8866cc"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01N2x8YNfnfHNbj6Mv1xNhVL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindTags;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagRepository;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.List;\n    10→\n    11→@Singleton\n    12→public class FindTagsImpl implements FindTags {\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    private TagRepository tagRepository;\n    16→\n    17→    @Override\n    18→    public List<Tag> handle() {\n    19→        return tagRepository.findAllTags();\n    20→    }\n    21→}\n    22→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BWvvuA8PXTmK3mv6UFCiMY","session_id":"df1561a9-af26-4e6c-a6ca-e235ecd783f5","uuid":"3d5dddda-0562-4bbc-bb4c-af8756b59323"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QyPjxQX9Rksm2KoreXpBQB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateTag;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindTagsByNameCreateIfNotExists;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagRepository;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.LinkedList;\n    11→import java.util.List;\n    12→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n    13→\n    14→@Singleton\n    15→public class FindTagsByNameCreateIfNotExistsImpl implements FindTagsByNameCreateIfNotExists {\n    16→\n    17→    @Inject\n    18→    private TagRepository tagRepository;\n    19→    @Inject\n    20→    private CreateTag createTag;\n    21→\n    22→    @Override\n    23→    public List<Tag> handle(List<String> names) {\n    24→        final var tags = tagRepository.findByNames(names);\n    25→        tags.addAll(createTags(nonexistent(tags, names)));\n    26→        return tags;\n    27→    }\n    28→\n    29→    private List<Tag> createTags(List<String> names) {\n    30→        final var tags = new LinkedList<Tag>();\n    31→        names.forEach(name -> tags.add(createTag.handle(name)));\n    32→        return tags;\n    33→    }\n    34→\n    35→    private List<String> nonexistent(List<Tag> existing, List<String> allNames) {\n    36→        return allNames.stream()\n    37→                .filter(name -> existing.stream().noneMatch(tag -> tag.getName().equalsIgnoreCase(name)))\n    38→                .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    39→    }\n    40→}\n    41→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BWvvuA8PXTmK3mv6UFCiMY","session_id":"df1561a9-af26-4e6c-a6ca-e235ecd783f5","uuid":"490cd564-001f-489a-b880-4219c8ead353"}
