{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01585N46DcmT1PUuz1YMyd8v","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.EmailAlreadyExistsException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.UsernameAlreadyExistsException;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.UpdateUser;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UpdateUserInput;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserRepository;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.validator.ModelValidator;\n    13→\n    14→import java.util.UUID;\n    15→\n    16→@Dependent\n    17→public class UpdateUserImpl implements UpdateUser {\n    18→\n    19→    @Inject\n    20→    private FindUserById findUserById;\n    21→    @Inject\n    22→    private UserRepository userRepository;\n    23→    @Inject\n    24→    private ModelValidator modelValidator;\n    25→\n    26→    @Override\n    27→    public User handle(UpdateUserInput updateUserInput) {\n    28→        final var user = findUserById.handle(updateUserInput.getId());\n    29→        checkValidations(updateUserInput, updateUserInput.getId());\n    30→        updateFields(user, updateUserInput);\n    31→        userRepository.update(modelValidator.validate(user));\n    32→        return user;\n    33→    }\n    34→\n    35→    private void updateFields(User user, UpdateUserInput updateUserInput) {\n    36→        if (isPresent(updateUserInput.getUsername())) {\n    37→            user.setUsername(updateUserInput.getUsername());\n    38→        }\n    39→\n    40→        if (isPresent(updateUserInput.getEmail())) {\n    41→            user.setEmail(updateUserInput.getEmail());\n    42→        }\n    43→\n    44→        if (isPresent(updateUserInput.getBio())) {\n    45→            user.setBio(updateUserInput.getBio());\n    46→        }\n    47→\n    48→        if (isPresent(updateUserInput.getImage())) {\n    49→            user.setImage(updateUserInput.getImage());\n    50→        }\n    51→    }\n    52→\n    53→    private void checkValidations(UpdateUserInput updateUserInput, UUID excludeId) {\n    54→\n    55→        if (isPresent(updateUserInput.getUsername())) {\n    56→            checkUsername(excludeId, updateUserInput.getUsername());\n    57→        }\n    58→\n    59→        if (isPresent(updateUserInput.getEmail())) {\n    60→            checkEmail(excludeId, updateUserInput.getEmail());\n    61→        }\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    private boolean isPresent(String property) {\n    65→        return property != null && !property.isEmpty();\n    66→    }\n    67→\n    68→    private void checkUsername(UUID selfId, String username) {\n    69→        if (userRepository.existsUsername(selfId, username)) {\n    70→            throw new UsernameAlreadyExistsException();\n    71→        }\n    72→    }\n    73→\n    74→    private void checkEmail(UUID selfId, String email) {\n    75→        if (userRepository.existsEmail(selfId, email)) {\n    76→            throw new EmailAlreadyExistsException();\n    77→        }\n    78→    }\n    79→}\n    80→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BWvvuA8PXTmK3mv6UFCiMY","session_id":"df1561a9-af26-4e6c-a6ca-e235ecd783f5","uuid":"102cc5ad-1a4c-4776-a8be-e4428f9e1979"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BWvvuA8PXTmK3mv6UFCiMY","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have now read all the requested files. Let me compile a comprehensive response with all the file contents organized by category.\n\n---\n\n# COMPLETE FILE CONTENTS - RealWorld API Application\n\nI've successfully read all 91 requested files. Below are the complete contents of each file, organized by category:\n\n## DOMAIN MODELS\n\n### Article Domain Models\n\n**1. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/domain/model/article/Article.java**\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article;\n\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\nimport lombok.AccessLevel;\nimport lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\nimport lombok.Data;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n\nimport java.time.LocalDateTime;\nimport java.util.UUID;\n\n@Data\n@AllArgsConstructor(access = AccessLevel.PROTECTED)\npublic class Article {\n  @NotNull private UUID id;\n  @NotBlank private String slug;\n\n  @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.TITLE_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n  private String title;\n\n  @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.DESCRIPTION_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n  private String description;\n\n  @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.BODY_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n  private String body;\n\n  @NotNull private LocalDateTime createdAt;\n  private LocalDateTime updatedAt;\n  @NotNull private User author;\n}\n```\n\n**2. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/domain/model/article/ArticleModelBuilder.java**\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article;\n\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.inject.Singleton;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.validator.ModelValidator;\n\nimport java.time.LocalDateTime;\nimport java.util.UUID;\n\n@Singleton\npublic class ArticleModelBuilder {\n\n    @Inject\n    private ModelValidator modelValidator;\n\n    public Article build(String slug, String title, String description, String body, User author) {\n        final var createdAt = LocalDateTime.now();\n        return modelValidator.validate(\n                new Article(\n                        UUID.randomUUID(), slug, title, description, body, createdAt, createdAt, author));\n    }\n\n    public Article build(\n            UUID id,\n            String slug,\n            String title,\n            String description,\n            String body,\n            LocalDateTime createdAt,\n            LocalDateTime updatedAt,\n            User author) {\n        return modelValidator.validate(\n                new Article(id, slug, title, description, body, createdAt, updatedAt, author));\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**3. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/domain/model/article/ArticleRepository.java**\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article;\n\nimport java.util.Optional;\nimport java.util.UUID;\n\npublic interface ArticleRepository {\n    boolean existsBySlug(String slug);\n\n    void save(Article article);\n\n    Optional<Article> findArticleById(UUID id);\n\n    Optional<Article> findBySlug(String slug);\n\n    void update(Article article);\n\n    Optional<Article> findByAuthorAndSlug(UUID authorId, String slug);\n\n    void delete(Article article);\n\n    PageResult<Article> findMostRecentArticlesByFilter(ArticleFilter articleFilter);\n\n    PageResult<Article> findArticlesByFilter(ArticleFilter filter);\n}\n```\n\n**4. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/domain/model/article/ArticleFilter.java**\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article;\n\nimport lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\nimport lombok.Data;\n\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.UUID;\n\n@Data\n@AllArgsConstructor\npublic class ArticleFilter {\n  private final int offset;\n  private final int limit;\n  private final UUID loggedUserId;\n  private final List<String> tags;\n  private final List<String> authors;\n  private final List<String> favorited;\n}\n```\n\n**5. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/domain/model/article/PageResult.java**\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article;\n\nimport lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\nimport lombok.Data;\n\nimport java.util.List;\n\n@Data\n@AllArgsConstructor\npublic class PageResult<T> {\n  private List<T> result;\n  private long total;\n}\n```\n\n**6. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/domain/model/article/NewArticleInput.java**\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article;\n\nimport lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\nimport lombok.Data;\n\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.UUID;\n\n@Data\n@AllArgsConstructor\npublic class NewArticleInput {\n  private UUID authorId;\n  private String title;\n  private String description;\n  private String body;\n  private List<String> tagList;\n}\n```\n\n**7. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/domain/model/article/UpdateArticleInput.java**\n```j