{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TzWxBMR7kxPzbYg9HUZNU2","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider;\n     2→\n     3→import at.favre.lib.crypto.bcrypt.BCrypt;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.HashProvider;\n     6→\n     7→@ApplicationScoped\n     8→public class BCryptHashProvider implements HashProvider {\n     9→\n    10→    @Override\n    11→    public String hashPassword(String password) {\n    12→        return BCrypt.withDefaults().hashToString(12, password.toCharArray());\n    13→    }\n    14→\n    15→    @Override\n    16→    public boolean checkPassword(String plaintext, String hashed) {\n    17→        return BCrypt.verifyer().verify(plaintext.toCharArray(), hashed).verified;\n    18→    }\n    19→}\n    20→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BDn9jiVzETnWraGJQhAeLr","session_id":"df1561a9-af26-4e6c-a6ca-e235ecd783f5","uuid":"a45de4bb-228b-44a0-b4ce-3b65a8099b97"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PUC8dcWbAztyTZFhoe7nR1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider;\n     2→\n     3→import com.auth0.jwt.JWT;\n     4→import com.auth0.jwt.JWTCreator;\n     5→import com.auth0.jwt.JWTVerifier;\n     6→import com.auth0.jwt.algorithms.Algorithm;\n     7→import com.auth0.jwt.interfaces.Claim;\n     8→import com.auth0.jwt.interfaces.DecodedJWT;\n     9→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    10→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    11→import org.eclipse.microprofile.config.inject.ConfigProperty;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.TokenProvider;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.profile.Role;\n    14→\n    15→import java.util.Calendar;\n    16→import java.util.Date;\n    17→import java.util.UUID;\n    18→\n    19→@ApplicationScoped\n    20→public class JwtTokenProvider implements TokenProvider {\n    21→\n    22→    private final String COMPLEMENTARY_SUBSCRIPTION = \"complementary-subscription\";\n    23→    private final String CLAIM_ROLES = \"ROLES\";\n    24→    private Algorithm algorithm;\n    25→    private JWTVerifier jwtVerifier;\n    26→    private String issuer;\n    27→    private Integer expirationTimeInMinutes;\n    28→\n    29→    @Inject\n    30→    public JwtTokenProvider(\n    31→            @ConfigProperty(name = \"jwt.issuer\") String issuer,\n    32→            @ConfigProperty(name = \"jwt.secret\") String secret,\n    33→            @ConfigProperty(name = \"jwt.expiration.time.minutes\") Integer expirationTimeInMinutes) {\n    34→\n    35→        this.issuer = issuer;\n    36→        this.algorithm = Algorithm.HMAC512(secret);\n    37→        this.jwtVerifier = JWT.require(algorithm).withIssuer(issuer).build();\n    38→        this.expirationTimeInMinutes = expirationTimeInMinutes;\n    39→    }\n    40→\n    41→    @Override\n    42→    public String createUserToken(String subject) {\n    43→        JWTCreator.Builder builder;\n    44→\n    45→        builder =\n    46→                JWT.create()\n    47→                        .withIssuer(issuer)\n    48→                        .withSubject(subject)\n    49→                        .withIssuedAt(new Date())\n    50→                        .withClaim(COMPLEMENTARY_SUBSCRIPTION, UUID.randomUUID().toString());\n    51→\n    52→        builder.withArrayClaim(CLAIM_ROLES, toArrayNames(Role.USER));\n    53→\n    54→        if (expirationTimeInMinutes != null) {\n    55→            builder.withExpiresAt(plusMinutes(expirationTimeInMinutes));\n    56→        }\n    57→\n    58→        return builder.sign(algorithm);\n    59→    }\n    60→\n    61→    @Override\n    62→    public DecodedJWT verify(String token) {\n    63→        return jwtVerifier.verify(token);\n    64→    }\n    65→\n    66→    @Override\n    67→    public Role[] extractRoles(DecodedJWT decodedJWT) {\n    68→        Claim claim = decodedJWT.getClaim(CLAIM_ROLES);\n    69→        return claim.asArray(Role.class);\n    70→    }\n    71→\n    72→    private static String[] toArrayNames(Role... allowedRoles) {\n    73→\n    74→        String[] names = new String[allowedRoles.length];\n    75→\n    76→        for (int nameIndex = 0; nameIndex < allowedRoles.length; nameIndex++) {\n    77→            names[nameIndex] = allowedRoles[nameIndex].name();\n    78→        }\n    79→\n    80→        return names;\n    81→    }\n    82→\n    83→    private static Date plusMinutes(int minutes) {\n    84→        int oneMinuteInMillis = 60000;\n    85→        Calendar calendar = Calendar.getInstance();\n    86→        return new Date(calendar.getTimeInMillis() + (minutes * oneMinuteInMillis));\n    87→    }\n    88→}\n    89→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BDn9jiVzETnWraGJQhAeLr","session_id":"df1561a9-af26-4e6c-a6ca-e235ecd783f5","uuid":"bcf70b4b-cf38-4b7f-8bea-28f14820bb9b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0153PTmBhRf1F1nznDDdy1xf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider;\n     2→\n     3→import com.github.slugify.Slugify;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.SlugProvider;\n     7→\n     8→\n     9→@ApplicationScoped\n    10→public class SlugifySlugProvider implements SlugProvider {\n    11→\n    12→    private Slugify slugify;\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    public SlugifySlugProvider() {\n    16→        this.slugify = Slugify.builder().build();\n    17→    }\n    18→\n    19→    @Override\n    20→    public String slugify(String text) {\n    21→        return slugify.slugify(text);\n    22→    }\n    23→}\n    24→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BDn9jiVzETnWraGJQhAeLr","session_id":"df1561a9-af26-4e6c-a6ca-e235ecd783f5","uuid":"25fbc76a-2ace-41b8-b6c4-e1f5ec41491d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DeKacbVkGGwLJwqtHpkUSc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.filter;\n     2→\n     3→import com.auth0.jwt.exceptions.JWTVerificationException;\n     4→import com.auth0.jwt.interfaces.DecodedJWT;\n     5→import jakarta.annotation.Priority;\n     6→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.Priorities;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.container.ContainerRequestContext;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.container.ContainerRequestFilter;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.container.ResourceInfo;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Context;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.HttpHeaders;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.Provider;\n    15→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.exception.UnauthorizedException;\n    16→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.TokenProvider;\n    17→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.annotation.Secured;\n    18→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.context.DecodedJWTSecurityContext;\n    19→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.context.EmptySecurityContext;\n    20→\n    21→import java.io.IOException;\n    22→import java.lang.reflect.Method;\n    23→\n    24→@Secured\n    25→@Provider\n    26→@Priority(Priorities.AUTHENTICATION)\n    27→public class AuthenticationFilter implements ContainerRequestFilter {\n    28→\n    29→    private final String AUTHORIZATION_HEADER_PREFIX = \"Token \";\n    30→\n    31→    @Inject\n    32→    TokenProvider tokenProvider;\n    33→\n    34→    @Context\n    35→    private ResourceInfo resourceInfo;\n    36→\n    37→    @Override\n    38→    public void filter(ContainerRequestContext containerRequestContext) throws IOException {\n    39→\n    40→        String authorizationHeader = containerRequestContext.getHeaderString(HttpHeaders.AUTHORIZATION);\n    41→\n    42→        if (authorizationHeader != null\n    43→                && authorizationHeader.startsWith(AUTHORIZATION_HEADER_PREFIX)) {\n    44→\n    45→            String token = authorizationHeader.replace(AUTHORIZATION_HEADER_PREFIX, \"\");\n    46→\n    47→            try {\n    48→\n    49→                DecodedJWT decodedJWT = tokenProvider.verify(token);\n    50→\n    51→                containerRequestContext.setSecurityContext(\n    52→                        new DecodedJWTSecurityContext(decodedJWT, tokenProvider));\n    53→\n    54→            } catch (JWTVerificationException ex) {\n    55→                containerRequestContext.abortWith(\n    56→                        Response.ok(Response.Status.UNAUTHORIZED.toString())\n    57→                                .status(Response.Status.UNAUTHORIZED)\n    58→                                .build());\n    59→            }\n    60→        } else {\n    61→\n    62→            containerRequestContext.setSecurityContext(new EmptySecurityContext());\n    63→\n    64→            if (!isSecurityOptional()) {\n    65→                throw new UnauthorizedException();\n    66→            }\n    67→        }\n    68→    }\n    69→\n    70→    private boolean isSecurityOptional() {\n    71→\n    72→        Class<?> resourceClass = resourceInfo.getResourceClass();\n    73→        Method resourceMethod = resourceInfo.getResourceMethod();\n    74→        Secured resourceClassSecured = resourceClass.getAnnotation(Secured.class);\n    75→        Secured resourceMethodSecured = resourceMethod.getAnnotation(Secured.class);\n    76→\n    77→        if (resourceMethodSecured != null) {\n    78→            return resourceMethodSecured.optional();\n    79→        }\n    80→\n    81→        if (resourceClassSecured != null) {\n    82→            return resourceClassSecured.optional();\n    83→        }\n    84→\n    85→        return false;\n    86→    }\n    87→}\n    88→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BDn9jiVzETnWraGJQhAeLr","session_id":"df1561a9-af26-4e6c-a6ca-e235ecd783f5","uuid":"342c7dfa-0e61-45a9-acb5-38d881ad2f9e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BRihEiUWho7bkapSSUbHtw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.filter;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.annotation.Priority;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.Priorities;\n     5→import jakarta.ws.rs.container.ContainerRequestContext;\n     6→import jakarta.ws.rs.container.ContainerRequestFilter;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.container.ResourceInfo;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Context;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.Provider;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.exception.ForbiddenException;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.annotation.Secured;\n    14→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.profile.Role;\n    15→\n    16→import java.io.IOException;\n    17→import java.lang.reflect.AnnotatedElement;\n    18→import java.lang.reflect.Method;\n    19→import java.util.Arrays;\n    20→import java.util.LinkedList;\n    21→import java.util.List;\n    22→\n    23→@Secured\n    24→@Provider\n    25→@Priority(Priorities.AUTHORIZATION)\n    26→public class AuthorizationFilter implements ContainerRequestFilter {\n    27→\n    28→    @Context\n    29→    private ResourceInfo resourceInfo;\n    30→\n    31→    @Override\n    32→    public void filter(ContainerRequestContext containerRequestContext) throws IOException {\n    33→\n    34→        Class<?> resourceClass = resourceInfo.getResourceClass();\n    35→        Method resourceMethod = resourceInfo.getResourceMethod();\n    36→\n    37→        if (!isSecurityOptional(resourceMethod, resourceClass)) {\n    38→            SecurityContext securityContext = containerRequestContext.getSecurityContext();\n    39→\n    40→            List<Role> classRoles = extractRoles(resourceClass);\n    41→            List<Role> methodRoles = extractRoles(resourceMethod);\n    42→\n    43→            try {\n    44→                if (methodRoles.isEmpty()) {\n    45→                    checkPermissions(classRoles, securityContext);\n    46→                } else {\n    47→                    checkPermissions(methodRoles, securityContext);\n    48→                }\n    49→            } catch (Exception ex) {\n    50→                containerRequestContext.abortWith(Response.status(Response.Status.FORBIDDEN).build());\n    51→            }\n    52→        }\n    53→    }\n    54→\n    55→    private boolean isSecurityOptional(Method resourceMethod, Class<?> resourceClass) {\n    56→        Secured resourceClassSecured = resourceClass.getAnnotation(Secured.class);\n    57→        Secured resourceMethodSecured = resourceMethod.getAnnotation(Secured.class);\n    58→\n    59→        if (resourceMethodSecured != null) {\n    60→            return resourceMethodSecured.optional();\n    61→        }\n    62→\n    63→        if (resourceClassSecured != null) {\n    64→            return resourceClassSecured.optional();\n    65→        }\n    66→\n    67→        return false;\n    68→    }\n    69→\n    70→    private void checkPermissions(List<Role> allowedRoles, SecurityContext securityContext) {\n    71→        if (!isAccessAllowed(allowedRoles, securityContext)) {\n    72→            throw new ForbiddenException();\n    73→        }\n    74→    }\n    75→\n    76→    private boolean isAccessAllowed(List<Role> allowedRoles, SecurityContext securityContext) {\n    77→        for (Role allowedRole : allowedRoles) {\n    78→            if (securityContext.isUserInRole(allowedRole.name())) {\n    79→                return true;\n    80→            }\n    81→        }\n    82→        return false;\n    83→    }\n    84→\n    85→    private List<Role> extractRoles(AnnotatedElement annotatedElement) {\n    86→        if (annotatedElement == null) {\n    87→            return new LinkedList<>();\n    88→        } else {\n    89→            Secured secured = annotatedElement.getAnnotation(Secured.class);\n    90→            if (secured == null) {\n    91→                return new LinkedList<>();\n    92→            } else {\n    93→                return Arrays.asList(secured.value());\n    94→            }\n    95→        }\n    96→    }\n    97→}\n    98→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BDn9jiVzETnWraGJQhAeLr","session_id":"df1561a9-af26-4e6c-a6ca-e235ecd783f5","uuid":"4ce1e0f2-f3ca-4c85-8de7-de6b160f9cbd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YB5n5aE54Ud4i3n2uc8K7C","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     6→import jakarta.validation.ConstraintViolationException;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.ExceptionMapper;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.Provider;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.ErrorResponse;\n    11→\n    12→@Provider\n    13→public class BeanValidationExceptionMapper\n    14→        implements ExceptionMapper<ConstraintViolationException> {\n    15→\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n    18→\n    19→    @Override\n    20→    public Response toResponse(ConstraintViolationException e) {\n    21→\n    22→        ErrorResponse errorResponse = new ErrorResponse();\n    23→\n    24→        e.getConstraintViolations()\n    25→                .iterator()\n    26→                .forEachRemaining(\n    27→                        contraint -> {\n    28→                            errorResponse.getBody().add(contraint.getMessage());\n    29→                        });\n    30→\n    31→        try {\n    32→            return Response.ok(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(errorResponse)).status(422).build();\n    33→        } catch (JsonProcessingException ex) {\n    34→            throw new RuntimeException(ex);\n    35→        }\n    36→    }\n    37→}\n    38→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BDn9jiVzETnWraGJQhAeLr","session_id":"df1561a9-af26-4e6c-a6ca-e235ecd783f5","uuid":"0b5f2cc6-fa96-4629-b87e-f59c60fad2c6"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RAGqSKTrLoUYL28VGpBmME","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleModelBuilder;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.TagRelationship;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentBuilder;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagBuilder;\n    14→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    15→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserModelBuilder;\n    16→\n    17→@ApplicationScoped\n    18→public class EntityUtils {\n    19→\n    20→    @Inject\n    21→    @Named(\"usermodelbuilder\")\n    22→    private UserModelBuilder userBuilder;\n    23→    @Inject\n    24→    private TagBuilder tagBuilder;\n    25→    @Inject\n    26→    private ArticleModelBuilder articleBuilder;\n    27→    @Inject\n    28→    private CommentBuilder commentBuilder;\n    29→\n    30→    public User user(UserEntity userEntity) {\n    31→        final var id = userEntity.getId();\n    32→        final var username = userEntity.getUsername();\n    33→        final var bio = userEntity.getBio();\n    34→        final var image = userEntity.getImage();\n    35→        final var password = userEntity.getPassword();\n    36→        final var email = userEntity.getEmail();\n    37→        return userBuilder.build(id, username, bio, image, password, email);\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    public Tag tag(TagEntity tagEntity) {\n    41→        return tagBuilder.build(tagEntity.getId(), tagEntity.getName());\n    42→    }\n    43→\n    44→    public Tag tag(TagRelationshipEntity tagRelationshipEntity) {\n    45→        return tag(tagRelationshipEntity.getTag());\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    public TagRelationship tagRelationship(TagRelationshipEntity tagRelationshipEntity) {\n    49→        return new TagRelationship(article(tagRelationshipEntity.getArticle()), tag(tagRelationshipEntity.getTag()));\n    50→    }\n    51→\n    52→    public Article article(ArticleEntity articleEntity) {\n    53→        return articleBuilder.build(\n    54→                articleEntity.getId(),\n    55→                articleEntity.getSlug(),\n    56→                articleEntity.getTitle(),\n    57→                articleEntity.getDescription(),\n    58→                articleEntity.getBody(),\n    59→                articleEntity.getCreatedAt(),\n    60→                articleEntity.getUpdatedAt(),\n    61→                user(articleEntity.getAuthor()));\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    public Comment comment(CommentEntity commentEntity) {\n    65→        return commentBuilder.build(\n    66→                commentEntity.getId(),\n    67→                user(commentEntity.getAuthor()),\n    68→                article(commentEntity.getArticle()),\n    69→                commentEntity.getBody(),\n    70→                commentEntity.getCreatedAt(),\n    71→                commentEntity.getUpdatedAt());\n    72→    }\n    73→\n    74→    public FavoriteRelationship favoriteRelationship(\n    75→            FavoriteRelationshipEntity favoriteRelationshipEntity) {\n    76→        return new FavoriteRelationship(\n    77→                user(favoriteRelationshipEntity.getUser()),\n    78→                article(favoriteRelationshipEntity.getArticle()));\n    79→    }\n    80→}\n    81→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BDn9jiVzETnWraGJQhAeLr","session_id":"df1561a9-af26-4e6c-a6ca-e235ecd783f5","uuid":"f96e1a35-6374-4282-a7a6-9b40c21da5e5"}
