{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01T7V3EPWnPi5AVsYzrZzT8w","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     5→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     6→import lombok.Getter;\n     7→import lombok.NoArgsConstructor;\n     8→import lombok.Setter;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\n    10→\n    11→@Getter\n    12→@Setter\n    13→@AllArgsConstructor\n    14→@NoArgsConstructor\n    15→public class UpdateUserRequestWrapper {\n    16→\n    17→    @Valid\n    18→    @NotNull(message = ValidationMessages.REQUEST_BODY_MUST_BE_NOT_NULL)\n    19→    private UpdateUserRequest user;\n    20→\n    21→}\n    22→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"df1561a9-af26-4e6c-a6ca-e235ecd783f5","uuid":"ceaea1e2-2918-4956-8e1b-ccfd49658d47"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01D5iYaR9RJBaFheq1xmFwnB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n     4→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     5→import lombok.Getter;\n     6→import lombok.NoArgsConstructor;\n     7→import lombok.Setter;\n     8→\n     9→@Getter\n    10→@Setter\n    11→@AllArgsConstructor\n    12→@NoArgsConstructor\n    13→public class NewCommentRequestWrapper {\n    14→\n    15→    @Valid\n    16→    private NewCommentRequest comment;\n    17→}\n    18→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"df1561a9-af26-4e6c-a6ca-e235ecd783f5","uuid":"89b3e22a-39d2-4f31-9cf9-d081376335ed"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_012d3rN7SoYqhcqYsSWt6SHz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete understanding. Here's the plan for fixing:\n\n**The core problem**: The primary `ObjectMapper` has `WRAP_ROOT_VALUE` and `UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE` enabled. This means:\n- Serialization: Every response object gets wrapped with its root name. `UserResponse` → `{\"user\": {...}}` (correct, has `@JsonRootName(\"user\")`), but `TagsResponse` → `{\"TagsResponse\": {\"tags\": [...]}}` (wrong, no `@JsonRootName`), `ArticlesResponse` → `{\"ArticlesResponse\": {\"articles\": ...}}` (wrong).\n- Deserialization: Request bodies need root unwrapping. `NewUserRequestWrapper` gets `{\"user\": {...}}` but with UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE, Jackson expects `{\"NewUserRequestWrapper\": {\"user\": {...}}}`.\n\n**The fix**: Disable `WRAP_ROOT_VALUE`/`UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE` globally. Instead, responses that need wrapping already handle it through their class structure (wrapper classes). For `UserResponse`, `ArticleResponse`, `CommentResponse`, `ProfileResponse` which have `@JsonRootName`, those are used in certain contexts where they need wrapping:\n- `UserResponse` - returned directly from controller → needs `{\"user\": {...}}`\n- `ArticleResponse` - returned from `resourceUtils.articleResponse()` → needs `{\"article\": {...}}`  \n- `ProfileResponse` - returned from profile endpoints → needs `{\"profile\": {...}}`\n- `CommentResponse` - returned from comment endpoints → needs `{\"comment\": {...}}`\n\nBut when `ArticleResponse` is nested inside `ArticlesResponse`, it should NOT be wrapped.\n\nThe cleanest approach: Remove WRAP_ROOT_VALUE and use simple Map-wrapping for single-object responses that need a root key.\n\nLet me implement the fixes:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3575,"cache_read_input_tokens":56503,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3575,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1058},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"df1561a9-af26-4e6c-a6ca-e235ecd783f5","uuid":"62220934-5c81-4945-81e9-ef310865d50b"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_012d3rN7SoYqhcqYsSWt6SHz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01Am9Pp4PKpjKq35ewNGF3Ax","name":"TodoWrite","input":{"todos":[{"content":"Analyze existing codebase structure","status":"completed","activeForm":"Analyzing existing codebase structure"},{"content":"Create new Spring Boot pom.xml with all dependencies","status":"completed","activeForm":"Creating Spring Boot pom.xml"},{"content":"Create Spring Boot application class and configuration","status":"completed","activeForm":"Creating Spring Boot application class"},{"content":"Migrate REST controllers from JAX-RS to Spring MVC","status":"completed","activeForm":"Migrating REST controllers"},{"content":"Migrate security (JWT filters) to Spring Security","status":"completed","activeForm":"Migrating security filters"},{"content":"Migrate DAOs from JPA EntityManager to Spring-compatible","status":"completed","activeForm":"Migrating DAOs"},{"content":"Migrate CDI annotations to Spring annotations across all files","status":"completed","activeForm":"Migrating CDI annotations"},{"content":"Migrate exception mappers to Spring @ControllerAdvice","status":"completed","activeForm":"Migrating exception mappers"},{"content":"Create application.properties for Spring Boot","status":"completed","activeForm":"Creating application.properties"},{"content":"Remove old Jakarta-specific files and update Dockerfile/start.sh","status":"completed","activeForm":"Removing old files and updating Dockerfile"},{"content":"Generate smoke tests","status":"completed","activeForm":"Generating smoke tests"},{"content":"Build Docker image and run container","status":"completed","activeForm":"Building and running Docker container"},{"content":"Fix Jackson serialization - disable WRAP_ROOT_VALUE, use explicit wrapping","status":"in_progress","activeForm":"Fixing Jackson serialization"},{"content":"Fix controllers to return properly wrapped responses","status":"pending","activeForm":"Fixing controller response wrapping"},{"content":"Fix error handler to return wrapped errors","status":"pending","activeForm":"Fixing error handler wrapping"},{"content":"Rebuild Docker and re-run smoke tests","status":"pending","activeForm":"Rebuilding and re-testing"},{"content":"Document all actions in CHANGELOG.md","status":"pending","activeForm":"Documenting in CHANGELOG.md"}]}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3575,"cache_read_input_tokens":56503,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3575,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1058},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"df1561a9-af26-4e6c-a6ca-e235ecd783f5","uuid":"1340baed-c25b-4c5f-bc3a-cf77186ebf5a"}
