{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_011E2evkePrMTZ6efz4NxB9E","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The migration is complete. Here's a summary:\n\n## Migration Complete: Jakarta EE → Spring Boot\n\n**All 23 smoke tests passing** with the application running in Docker.\n\n### What was done:\n1. **Build system**: Replaced Jakarta EE/MicroProfile/Liberty Maven dependencies with Spring Boot 3.4.1 starters; changed packaging from WAR to JAR\n2. **Entry point**: Converted JAX-RS `Application` to `@SpringBootApplication`\n3. **REST controllers**: Migrated 5 controllers from JAX-RS to Spring MVC annotations\n4. **Security**: Replaced JAX-RS `ContainerRequestFilter` with Spring `HandlerInterceptor`\n5. **DI annotations**: Converted all CDI annotations (`@ApplicationScoped`, `@Inject`, etc.) to Spring equivalents across 40+ files\n6. **Exception handling**: Replaced 3 JAX-RS `ExceptionMapper` classes with a single `@RestControllerAdvice`\n7. **Configuration**: Created `application.properties` replacing persistence.xml, microprofile-config.properties, and server.xml\n8. **Cleanup**: Removed 12 obsolete files (JAX-RS filters, CDI qualifiers, Liberty config, etc.)\n\n### Bug fix during testing:\n- The initial ObjectMapper configuration with `WRAP_ROOT_VALUE`/`UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE` caused malformed JSON responses. Fixed by disabling global root wrapping and using explicit `Collections.singletonMap()` wrapping in controllers, matching the RealWorld API JSON format."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":662,"cache_read_input_tokens":100550,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":662,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":365},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"df1561a9-af26-4e6c-a6ca-e235ecd783f5","uuid":"83cef52a-65be-4e61-8f33-53e2ca504397"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":2269097,"duration_api_ms":2927453,"num_turns":143,"result":"The migration is complete. Here's a summary:\n\n## Migration Complete: Jakarta EE → Spring Boot\n\n**All 23 smoke tests passing** with the application running in Docker.\n\n### What was done:\n1. **Build system**: Replaced Jakarta EE/MicroProfile/Liberty Maven dependencies with Spring Boot 3.4.1 starters; changed packaging from WAR to JAR\n2. **Entry point**: Converted JAX-RS `Application` to `@SpringBootApplication`\n3. **REST controllers**: Migrated 5 controllers from JAX-RS to Spring MVC annotations\n4. **Security**: Replaced JAX-RS `ContainerRequestFilter` with Spring `HandlerInterceptor`\n5. **DI annotations**: Converted all CDI annotations (`@ApplicationScoped`, `@Inject`, etc.) to Spring equivalents across 40+ files\n6. **Exception handling**: Replaced 3 JAX-RS `ExceptionMapper` classes with a single `@RestControllerAdvice`\n7. **Configuration**: Created `application.properties` replacing persistence.xml, microprofile-config.properties, and server.xml\n8. **Cleanup**: Removed 12 obsolete files (JAX-RS filters, CDI qualifiers, Liberty config, etc.)\n\n### Bug fix during testing:\n- The initial ObjectMapper configuration with `WRAP_ROOT_VALUE`/`UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE` caused malformed JSON responses. Fixed by disabling global root wrapping and using explicit `Collections.singletonMap()` wrapping in controllers, matching the RealWorld API JSON format.","session_id":"df1561a9-af26-4e6c-a6ca-e235ecd783f5","total_cost_usd":29.808517959999982,"usage":{"input_tokens":1825,"cache_creation_input_tokens":393373,"cache_read_input_tokens":6614218,"output_tokens":57238,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":393373}},"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929":{"inputTokens":4098,"outputTokens":121861,"cacheReadInputTokens":31